        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 7:53PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 753 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northwest of Valentine National
Wildlife Refuge to near Norden. Movement was south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Valentine, Norden, Valentine National Wildlife Refuge, Merritt
Reservoir, Wood Lake, Smith Falls State Park, Schlagel Creek State
Wildlife Management Area, Highway 97 crossing the Niobrara River,
North River Trail, Sparks, and Big Alkali Lake State Wildlife
Management Area.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 183 between mile markers 126 and 221.
Highway 20 between mile markers 195 and 224.
Highway 97 between mile markers 110 and 124, near mile marker 126,
and between mile markers 130 and 141.
Highway 83 between mile markers 181 and 214.
Highway 12 between mile markers 1 and 48, and between mile markers
57 and 61.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
